      "writtenOn": "2021-04-06T13:37:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is perf, but by way of solving an ownership problem. When using GrTextBlobCache the GrAtlasTextOp::Geometry has a many to one relationship with the sub runs. When in cache bypass mode, there is a 1:1 relationship between the Geometry and the sub run. This means that Geometry can be a member of the sub run avoiding an allocation. In the end, this allows the ~GrAtlasTextOp() to handle destructing the Geometries in the same way.",
      "parentUuid": "22e9a0ed_f2c1919a",
